<br>
I believe by saying &quot;abusing&quot; you are actually meaning &quot;exploiting&quot;.  &quot;Exploiting&quot; is the use of spell side effects, the unintended use of spells in a given situation, or the use of game geography so that an undesigned or unforseen result would occur.  CotH was out LONG before PoP.  How can using a spell's normal effect be considered an &quot;exploit&quot;?  And lets face it, you can't get a more straight foreward spell than CotH (move groupmember from point A to point B...).  They knew the spell was there, they knew how it would be used, and honestly I don't think they really cared until someone started screaming &quot;FOUL!!&quot; loud enough to attract attention.  Once again, the squeaky wheel brings the nerf.<br>
